reviewText:
I lived in County Clare on the west coast of Ireland for 5 or so years and
this was a Brilliant Doc... could watch it 5 more times or more ;)
This documentary is entertaining i would give it a 5 but the Irish dialect is so thick at parts you need a subtitles to understand  but i still enjoyed this film
i have purchased a dozen copies and given them to friends.they all love it.
Most enjoyable for anyone who enjoys an Irish pub. Was received very quickly.
We saw this as at the Savannah Film Festival this past week and it was wonderful. Nicely shot. Great editing. Insightful, poignant at times and funny. Will watch again!
A charming peaceful documentary of the dying industry and culture of the old pubs of Ireland.  Pop and butter the popcorn and sit down and dream of travel!
Loved it!!
Great show!
Love those pub people.
Excellent insight to Irish pub life, as seen by the owner or head bartender.

If you are planning on visiting Ireland, watching this is a "must".  Thanks to this presentation, we were able to visit two of the pubs in the documentary and had a greater appreciation of their role in the local culture.
Bought this for friends that just travelled to Ireland.  They recognized many of the places.  I've never been there but found the video very entertaining.
Fantastic! Can't wait to go to Ireland and check them all!!!

This is a un little documentary about a series of pubs spread across the Emerald Isle. The film is professionally done, with excellent production values & interviews with a fine collection of interesting & colorful folk. I'm thankful it was subtitled because some of the accents are very strong.
brilliant
Thoroughly  enjoyed this movie.  If you  love Ireland or have wondered about the pub scene this film is brilliant

Wonderful documentary.  I would recommend to anyone who is planning a visit, especially since you
may have the opportunity to hoist a pint in one.  Myself, I am fond of the smaller pubs, with no blaring
television or music to spoil the experience.
Never watched the whole show.
Interesting show

I give it three stars vs. two star only because I've been to a pub and greatly enjoy the peculiarities of such an establishment.  Enjoyed the 1st 30 minutes, but it did get a bit tiring after a while.
Great movie. Wonderful portrayal of Irish pubs
Great primer for our upcoming trip to our ancestors land. Will not look like a complete ass maybe just a 1/2
The streaming download was had sporadic skips but there was enough to enjoy. Having spent some time in Dublin and Dingle Pubs, it brought back great memories.
VERY GOOD  THE OLD TIMES NOT FORGOTTEN

Fun DVD. Passed it along to a fellow that left Ireland some 50 years ago...he got quite a kick out of it.
Recommended if you like the idea of an older bar with character and characters.
Very well done. Highly recommended. One might make sure to have some Guinness on hand if watching this gem.
Wonderful!
Very good

If you've been to Ireland this will take you back to the land of perfect pubs. If you haven't, this will give you a grand taste of what's waiting for in Ireland. By chance and happenstance, I've been to a number of these pubs. This is a wonderful way to relive the visits. The "craic" is massive and I can't wait to go again.  Thank goodness for the subtitles.
Lovely, but I would have preferred more music, as in a few more Irish traditional music sessions. But I enjoyed the conversations and the history and the ambience of the pubs and the people.
Absolutely brilliant. A great look at what true Irish pubs in Ireland are like.
This doc. makes we want to visit each and every pub featured!
Awesome, entertaining, and really brings the true spirit of Ireland to you!!

I enjoyed this film very much.  Imagine, Ireland is so small, and so beautiful; yet, it has given the world so much in terns of literature, music, and song.  And, of course, there is the culture of Irish people, like its music, never dies.  Thank you.
Excellent stories of Irish families that carry out traditions that transcend time. It made me proud to be an Irishman.
Great insight into the Irish pub life, fascinating movie overall.
Not as entertaining as I hoped. A bit slow and anticlimactic.

A story about the TRUE Irish pub.
Fantastic documentary.
This movie is a favorite. Visited John B. Keane's on a recent trip to Ireland. Amazing!
Saw program on Netflix and decided I needed DVDs for friends to enjoy as well

Oh, I was bummed when it ended, I love pub culture. I wish there was more docs like that, they went all thru Ireland and found hidden gems. But only 3 in Dublin, and those have material for hours and hours, the ones linked to the revolution, to Ulysses and to the times of the troubles! Congrats, toltally but I would love more
It was cool to see this simple documentary interviewing pub owners of historic pubs all over Ireland. You really get a taste for the country and the the people and keeping up with traditions.
I love this vid and plan to purchase it.
great movie about Irish pubs.  worth watching!!
Priceless.
